name: Herring Gull
description: I've found people either love or loathe seagulls, I am quite strongly in the second camp. However, they do make wonderful subjects for photography due to their size and willingness to pose. They are absolutely everywhere in Brighton, and are always poised to steal a chip, pasty, or anything else you might be trying to enjoy. | 2592x3888px | f/8, 1/500s, 290mm | Canon 400D and Lightroom | Photographed 26th May 2021 just outside my house in Brighton, England
